$S_2 = \tau\,r$ & $V_2 = \frac{1}{2}\tau\,r^2$ & $S_3 = 2\tau\,r^2$ & $V_3 = \frac{2}{3} \tau\,r^3$ \smallskip \\ 
$S_4 = \frac{1}{2}\tau^2 r^3$ & $V_4 = \frac{1}{2\cdot 4}\tau^2 r^4$ & $S_5 = \frac{2}{3} \tau^2 r^4$ & $V_5 =\frac{2}{3\cdot 5} \tau^2 r^5$ \smallskip \\ 
